  "text": "It was interesting to find that the parietal lobe was slightly (~2%) larger on the left. We consider this to be driven by leftward asymmetries of the postCG and SMG, and it may well be related to the majority of subjects being right handed (left-hemisphere dominant). Previously, this slight leftward asymmetry has been reported by some authors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , but no asymmetry has been found by others [CITATION_3] .",
